// Z3 architecture
// 
// Memory: 64 words x 22 bits
//   1 bit sign
//   7 bit exponent  
//   14 bit mantissa
// 
// Instructions (8 types):
//   Ld n  - Load from memory n
//   St n  - Store to memory n  
//   +, -, *, /  - Arithmetic
//   sqrt  - Square root
// 
// Clock: 5.33 Hz (operations/second)

// Floating-point representation
// 
// Number: Â±M Ã— 2^E
//   M = mantissa (1.xxxxx in binary)
//   E = exponent (power of 2)
// 
// Example: 6.5 decimal
//   Binary: 110.1 = 1.101 Ã— 2^2
//   Sign: 0 (positive)
//   Exponent: 2 (with bias)
//   Mantissa: 101 (after leading 1)
// 
// Range: ~10^-38 to ~10^38 (32-bit)

